  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd 57 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Emergency Ordinance 57 is passed by a majority vote",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Emergency Act was implemented during the tenure of President Ranil Wickremesinghe as Acting President. If it is not passed by Parliament within 14 days, it will become null and void.",
        "In this case, the motion to extend the Emergency Act was presented in the Parliament and the related discussion took place till today evening.",
        "The emergency law was then put to a vote this evening, with 120 votes in favor and 63 votes against.",
        "Accordingly, the Emergency Act has been passed by 57 more votes and the Emergency Act will remain in force for another month."
      ],
